cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI 

The paper discusses a procedure for generating a stochastic dynamical model for populations of Thermostatically Controlled Loads (TCL) and investigates the problem of global regulation and load balancing. This involves concepts from control systems (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.MA), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and statistical inference (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of formal abstractions, which is a common technique in the field of formal methods (cs.SI).
